# Content standards

- New subagents, skills, and prompts must describe purpose, input, output, and constraints.
- Document security and error handling where relevant.
- Use clear metadata fields in Markdown/YAML frontmatter when required by the artifact type.
- Keep descriptions short, concrete, and actionable.
- Avoid unnecessary visual embellishments or emoticons in documentation.
- Do not add comments in JSON files.
